<topic id="marking-validation-errors">
  <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Text editing mode<indexterm>Validation errors</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Validation errors in Text mode</indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Validation<indexterm>Text
          Mode</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Validating XML Documents<indexterm>Text Mode</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_lfz_bgk_54b">By default, <ph keyref="product"/>
      <xref href="automatic-validation.dita#automatic-validation">automatically validates
        documents</xref> while editing in the <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode, and actions are also
      available to <xref
        href="validation-actions-in-user-interface.dita#validation-actions-in-user-interface"
        >manually validate documents</xref> on-request.</p>
    <p id="p_mfz_bgk_54b">
      <fig id="figure-automatic-validation-oxygen" product="editor author developer">
        <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_continous_validation.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_nfz_bgk_54b">
      <fig id="figure-automatic-validation-oxygenEclipse"
        product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">
        <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_continous_validation.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <section id="validation_marker_locations">
      <title>Validation Marker Locations</title>
      <p id="p_ofz_bgk_54b">In <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode, validation issues are marked in the following locations:<ul id="ul_pfz_bgk_54b">
          <li id="li_qfz_bgk_54b" irina="irina">In the main editing pane, with the issue underlined in a color according to the type
            of issue.</li>
          <li id="li_rfz_bgk_54b" irina="irina">In the right-side vertical stripe, with a marker that is colored according to the type
            of issue.</li>
          <li id="li_sfz_bgk_54b" irina="irina">For attributes with detected issues, in the <xref
              href="attributes-panel.dita#attributes-panel"><uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol>
              view</xref>, with the attribute and its value colored according to the type of
            issue.</li>
        </ul></p>
    </section>
    <section id="validation_marker_colors">
      <title>Validation Marker Colors</title>
      <p id="p_tfz_bgk_54b">The colors for each type of issue are as follows:<ul
          conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/ul-validation-markers" id="ul_ufz_bgk_54b">
          <li id="li_vfz_bgk_54b" irina="irina"/>
        </ul><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-doc-pref-link"/><ph
          conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-annotations-pref-eclipse"/></p>
    </section>
    <section id="validation_markers_in_the_rightside_stripe">
      <title>Validation Markers in the Right-Side Stripe</title>
      <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-stripe" id="p_wfz_bgk_54b"/>
    </section>
    <section id="hovering_over_validation_issues">
      <title>Hovering Over Validation Issues</title>
      <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-hovering" id="p_xfz_bgk_54b"/>
    </section>
    <section id="details_about_validation_issues">
      <title>Details About Validation Issues</title>
      <p id="p_yfz_bgk_54b">
        <ul id="ul_zfz_bgk_54b">
          <li id="li_agz_bgk_54b" irina="irina">Information about the issue is also displayed in the message area on the bottom of the
            editor panel (clicking the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Options16.png"/>Document
              checking options</uicontrol> button opens the <xref
              href="preferences-editor-document-checking.dita"><uicontrol>Document
                Checking</uicontrol> preferences page</xref> where you can configure some validation
              options<ph product="author developer editor"> (such as the colors used to present the
              validation issues)</ph>. Some validation messages have an icon (<image
              href="../img/Specs16.png" id="image_pgg_wcz_3mb"/>) and clicking it opens a dialog box
            with additional information and a link to specifications.</li>
          <li product="author developer editor" id="li_bgz_bgk_54b" irina="irina">When a validation is processed, information about
            the validation scenario is displayed in the stripe at the very bottom of the
            application. It includes the name of the validation scenario and its status. If you
            hover over the information, a tooltip is presented with more information. You can also
            click the <image href="../img/Information16.png" id="image_ib2_fnq_qlb"/> button to open
            the <xref href="../topics/view-status-information.dita"
                ><uicontrol>Information</uicontrol> view</xref>, where even more details are
                displayed.<p id="p_cgz_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/validation-tooltip.png" id="image_izh_mnq_qlb"
              /></p></li>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/EC-console-view"
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_dgz_bgk_54b" irina="irina"/>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/results-view" product="author developer editor" id="li_egz_bgk_54b" irina="irina"/>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/EC-results-view"
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse" id="li_fgz_bgk_54b" irina="irina"/>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </section>
